Is Heritrix doing anything else at this time?  How many other
fetches/threads are running concurrently?  If only one thread, do you
get the timeout?  

RecordingInputStream#read records all read from the socket to a file.
 Maybe its this writing to a file that is taking a long time?  Try
commenting out the recording in RecordingInputStream#read or maybe add
logging of how long its taking to complete ... especially if its
taking seconds to write bytes:

    public int read(byte[] b) throws IOException {
    	    if (!isOpen()) {
    	    	    throw new IOException(&quot;Stream closed &quot; +
    			    Thread.currentThread().getName());
    	    }
    	    int count = this.in.read(b);
-        if (count &gt; 0) {
-            assert this.recordingOutputStream != null: &quot;ROS is null &quot; - +
-                Thread.currentThread().getName();
-            this.recordingOutputStream.write(b,0,count);
-        }
        return count;
    }

Comment out the lines marked with &#39;-&#39; (this will break subsequent
processing of the file) or perhaps rather add a:

long startTime = System.currentMillis();

before the call to write with a logger.warn after the write that
reports how long the write took.

This is an interesting issue.  It shouldn&#39;t be behaving this way.
